{
  "stem": "11882.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We earned [GERMAN]-- that's about $0.30 an hour.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But we were getting teaching experience, and it was enough to live on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And so we rather neglected these Jewish families down in other parts of Germany who were waiting for us to come and teach them and their children something of English.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But gradually, one after another, we went down and lived with them for a time, as I did.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I went down in '38-- this is Hitler Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I, you must remember, was really quite ignorant of all this politics.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I could speak only a handful of words of German.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I could barely read a few headlines in the newspaper.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were protected.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were a foreign school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The top of the school, Herr Director Sander in Hamburg, had his breast covered with medals of German National Socialist Party, more or less a cover for his very fine business there.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But he had all these strange foreigners there-- British people, Australians, French, making money, making their little bit of money, teaching the language that they had.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "When-- we went down, then, when business got poor.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And business got very poor at a rather horrifying time, you probably have heard about, called Crystal Night-- when they went through the towns, these Nazis, because a German-- a German diplomat, a minor German diplomat, had been murdered in the German embassy in Paris.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They took vengeance, allegedly-- just wild destructiveness, went through the town, broke all the businesses'-- the windows.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The streets were all full of broken windows, broken glass.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And our students were very largely arrested, because it was predominantly what Hitler would call Jewish students.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They may or may not have been baptized Lutherans or once in a while Catholics.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
